irst=Shira|date=5 January 2015|website=HollywoodLife.com|publisher=[[Bonnie Fuller]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=14 November 2017}}</ref>) is an American actress and singer-songwriter. From 2006 to 2012 original run she starred in the TBS sitcom ''[[Tyler Perry's House of Payne]]'', a BET revival of the show was announced for 2020. Her other series regular roles include Tv One sitcom ''[[The Rickey Smiley Show]]'', Bounce TV prime time soap opera ''[[Saints & Sinners (2016 TV series)|Saints & Sinners]]'' and [[Syfy]] horror drama ''[[Superstition (TV series)|Superstition]]''.\n\nHer stage credits include playing [[Coretta Scott King]] in the Rhythm and Blues Opera ''[[I Dream (musical)|I Dream]]'' (2010), and well as role of Deena Jones in ''[[Dreamgirls]]'' (2012).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/article/STAGE-TUBE-Meet-Demetria-McKinney-Deena-in-The-Munys-DREAMGIRLS-20120717|title=STAGE TUBE: Meet Demetria McKinney - 'Deena' in The Muny's DREAMGIRLS!|first=Stage|last=Tube|publisher=|accessdate=14 November 2017}}</ref> In 2017, McKinney played [[Whitney Houston]] in the [[TV One (American TV channel)|TV One]] film ''[[Bobbi Kristina (film)|Bobbi Kristina]]''. She released her debut album ''Officially Yours'' in 2017.\n\n== Career ==\n===Acting===\nMcKinney performed in a number of [[Tyler Perry]]'s stage plays, including ''[[What's Done in the Dark|What\u2019s Done In The Dark]]'', ''[[Why Did I Get Married? (play)|Why Did I Get Married]]'', and ''[[A Madea Christmas (musical play)|Madea's Family Christmas]]''. She starred as Janine Shelton-Payne on the TBS comedy series ''[[Tyler Perry's House of Payne]]'' from 2006 to 2012. She was nominated for a 2009 National Association for Multi-ethnicity in Communications (NAMIC) Vision Award for Best Performance in a Comedy, in recognition of her work on ''House of Payne''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.namic.com/events/awards/downloads/NAMIC2009VANomsRlsFINAL.pdf |title=Nominees Announced for NAMIC Vision Awards Recognizing Diversity in Television Programming |publisher=Namic.com |date=2008-02-11 |accessdate=2014-02-08 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222020548/http://www.namic.com/events/awards/downloads/NAMIC2009VANomsRlsFINAL.pdf |archivedate=2014-02-22 }}</ref> She returned for her in the ''House of Payne'' spin-off ''[[The Paynes]]'' in 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://everythinggirlslove.com/egl-exclusive-demetria-mckinney-discusses-the-return-of-the-paynes-her-forthcoming-album-donald-trump-and-more/|title=EGL EXCLUSIVE: Demetria McKinney Discusses the Return of \"The Paynes,\" Her Forthcoming Album, Donald Trump and More!Everything Girls Love - Everything Girls Love|first=|last=admin|website=everythinggirlslove.com|accessdate=14 November 2017}}</ref> McKinney also guest starred on ''[[Necessary Roughness (TV series)|Necessary Roughness]]'', ''[[Drop Dead Diva]]'', ''[[Devious Maids]]'', ''[[Chicago Med]]'', and ''[[Being Mary Jane]]''. She has been a guest star on ''[[The Real Housewives of Atlanta]]'' airing on the [[Bravo (U.S. TV network)|Bravo]] Television Network since its 7th season premiere on November 9, 2014.\n\nFrom 2012 to 2014, McKinney had series regular role on the TV One comedy series, ''[[The Rickey Smiley Show]]''. In 2016, she was cast as Tamara Austin in the [[Bounce TV]] prime time television soap opera ''[[Saints & Sinners (2016 TV series)|Saints & Sinners]]''. In 2017, she was cast opposite [[Mario Van Peebles]] and [[Robinne Lee]] in the Syfy horror drama ''[[Superstition (TV series)|Superstition]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/07/superstition-mario-van-peebles-drama-cast-robinne-lee-brad-james-syfy-netflix-xlrator-media-1202139403/|title=\u2018Superstition\u2019: Syfy Drama From Mario Van Peebles, XLRator Sets Cast; Netflix Boards|first=Nancy|last=Tartaglione|date=31 July 2017|publisher=|accessdate=14 November 2017}}</ref> She series was canceled after one season, Also in 2017, McKinney starred in the TV One movie ''[[Bobbi Kristina (film)|Bobbi Kristina]]'' as [[Whitney Houston]], the late icon and mother to [[Bobbi Kristina Brown|Bobbi Kristina]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.essence.com/celebrity/demetria-mckinney-whitney-houston|title=Demetria McKinney Became The Most Vulnerable She's Ever Been For Her Role As Whitney Houston|publisher=|accessdate=14 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://people.com/music/bobbi-kristina-brown-made-for-tv-movie/|title=Bobbi Kristina Brown\u2019s Life Gets the Made-for-TV Biopic Treatment: See the First Cast Shot|date=28 April 2017|publisher=|accessdate=14 November 2017}}</ref>\n\nMcKinney had a recurring role in the BET drama series ''[[The Quad (TV series)|The Quad]]'' from 2017 to 2018. She played a leading role in the 2018 Christmas romantic film ''A Stone Cold Christmas''. In 2019, she starred in the [[Urban Movie Channel]] family drama series ''[[A House Divided (TV series)|A House Divided]]'' alongside [[Paula Jai Parker]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/a-house-divided-craig-ross-jrs-monogamy-umc-1203175041/|title=UMC Sets New Drama \u2018A House Divided,\u2019 \u2018Craig Ross Jr.\u2019s Monogamy\u2019 Season 2|first1=Rachel|last1=Yang|first2=Rachel|last2=Yang|date=March 28, 2019}}</ref> She later was cast in the [[Freeform (TV channel)|Freeform]] drama series ''[[Motherland: Fort Salem]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/motherland-freeform-series-regular-cast-1202424179/|title=\u2018Motherland\u2019: Freeform Sets Cast For Drama Pilot From \u2018Claws\u2019 Creator, Begins Production|first1=Denise|last1=Petski|first2=Denise|last2=Petski|date=July 10, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Singing===\nMcKinney performed in a number of musicals. She performed in the Rhythm and Blues Opera ''[[I Dream (opera)|I Dream]]'' in 2010. She appeared in ''[[Dreamgirls]]'' which she performed with [[Jennifer Holliday]] in 2012 and lent vocals to R&B singer [[Anthony David (singer)|Anthony David]]'s album ''Love Out Loud''.<ref name=aaa>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/demetria-mckinney-mn0003020529/biography|title=Demetria McKinney &#124; Biography & History|website=AllMusic}}</ref> In 2015 her single \"Trade It All\" charted on ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'''s [[Adult R&B Songs]].<ref name=aaa/>\n\nIn 2017, McKinney released her debut album ''Officially Yours''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theatlantavoice.com/articles/demetria-mckinney-new-projects/|title=The many shades of Demetria McKinney|website=www.theatlantavoice.com|accessdate=14 November 2017}}</ref> She She received nomination for [[NAACP Image Award for Outstanding New Artist]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://harlemworldmag.com/demetria-mckinney-nominated-naacp-image-award-comes-apollo/|title=Demetria McKinney Nominated For NAACP Image Award And Comes To The Apollo - Harlem World Magazine|date=21 November 2017|publisher=|accessdate=3 December 2017}}</ref> From this album, she released three singles: \"Is This Love\", \"Happy\" and \"Easy\" that peaked at #4 at the [[Adult R&B Songs]].<ref name=\"USR&B\"/>\n\n== Personal life ==\nMcKinney faced homelessness at the age of 17 and has one child.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://blackamericaweb.com/2015/06/12/demetria-mckinney-on-overcoming-homelessness-abuse-video/|title=Demetria McKinney on Overcoming Homelessness, Abuse [VIDEO]|date=2015-06-12|website=Black America Web|access-date=2016-07-08}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n=== Film ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n|-\n! Year\n! Film\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''Tyler Perry\u2019s Meet The Browns''\n| Kim Brown\n| Play\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''Tyler Perry\u2019s Why Did I Get Married?''\n| Trina\n| Play\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Daddy's Little Girls]] ''\n| Club Lady \n|  \n|-\n| 2007\n| ''Standing Reign''\n|Reign\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''Before I Wake''\n| Tracy Mason\n| Short film\n|-\n|2010\n| ''[[Breaking Up Is Hard to Do (film)|Breaking Up Is Hard 